ology)|zh|Ra (Egyptian Mythology)|lt=Ra|lt_de=Re|lt_ja=Ra|lt_zh=Ra}}'' every morning. |- | Royal Coronation Festival | As an annual renewal following the completion of a {{ill|Ecliptic#Introduction|de|Ekliptik#Einführung|ja|Ecliptic#Introduction|zh|Ecliptic#Introduction|lt=Solar Path|lt_de=Sonnenbahn|lt_ja=Solar Path|lt_zh=Solar Path}} marking the beginning of a new cycle. |- | {{ill|Min Festival|de|Min-Fest|ja|Min Festival|zh|Min Festival}} | Royal renewal and confirmation festival. |- | {{ill|Sokar Festival|de|Sokar-Fest|ja|Sokar Festival|zh|Sokar Festival}} | Royal renewal and confirmation festival. |- | {{ill|Neheb-kau Festival|de|Neheb-kau-Fest|ja|Neheb-kau Festival|zh|Neheb-kau Festival}} | Royal renewal and confirmation festival with New Year characteristics. |- | {{ill|Valley Festival|de|Talfest|ja|Valley Festival|zh|Valley Festival|lt=Valley Festival|lt_de=Tal-Fest|lt_ja=Valley Festival|lt_zh=Valley Festival}} | {{ill|New Kingdom|de|Neues Reich|ja|New Kingdom|zh|New Kingdom}}: royal renewal and confirmation festival. |- | {{ill|Amun-Re Festival|de|Amun-Re-Fest|ja|Amun-Re Festival|zh|Amun-Re Festival}} | New Kingdom: royal renewal and confirmation festival. |- | {{ill|Opet Festival|de|Opet-Fest|ja|Opet Festival|zh|Opet Festival}} | New Kingdom: royal renewal and confirmation festival. |- | {{ill|Sed Festival|de|Sedfest|ja|Sed Festival|zh|Sed Festival|lt=Sed Festival|lt_de=Sed-Fest|lt_ja=Sed Festival|lt_zh=Sed Festival}} | Royal renewal and confirmation festival. |- | Death of the King | Burial by his designated successor and transition into the {{ill|Duat|de|Duat|ja|Duat|zh|Duat}} as ''son of {{ill|Osiris|de|Osiris|ja|Osiris|zh|Osiris}}''. |- |}
