'''King&#39;s Festival Calendar''' is an ancient Egyptian festival ==Overview== The {{ill|Ancient Egypt|de|Altes Ägypten|ja|Ancient Egypt|zh|Ancient Egypt|lt=Ancient Egyptian|lt_de=altägyptische|lt_ja=Ancient Egyptian|lt_zh=Ancient Egyptian|12=draft}} '''King's Festival Calendar''' (also '''Royal Festivals, Renewal Festivals''') comprised only {{ill|Procession|de|Prozession|ja|Procession|zh|Procession|12=draft}}s, which served to confirm and renew the reigning ruler.
== Background == === Designation and Renewal === The priesthood designated as royal festivals only those celebrations exclusively reserved for the reigning ruler:
{| class="wikitable" style="width: 100%; border: 2px solid gray;" |- {{Ägyptologie TblHighlight}} ! width="25%" | Festival Types ! width="67%" | Content Specifications |- | Divine Legitimation | After the coronation, used only as a written reference to the divine election, without a public celebration. |- | {{ill|Designation|de|Designation|ja|Designation|zh|Designation|lt=King's Designation|lt_de=Bestimmung des Königs|lt_ja=King's Designation|lt_zh=King's Designation|12=draft}} | The reigning king designates his successor. Rarely: designation by {{ill|Ennead of Heliopolis|de|Neunheit von Heliopolis|ja|Ennead of Heliopolis|zh|Ennead of Heliopolis|lt=Divine Oracle|lt_de=Gottesorakel|lt_ja=Divine Oracle|lt_zh=Divine Oracle|12=draft}}. |- | {{ill|Enthronement in Ancient Egypt|de|Thronbesteigung im Alten Ägypten|ja|Enthronement in Ancient Egypt|zh|Enthronement in Ancient Egypt|lt=Enthronement Festival|lt_de=Thronbesteigungsfest|lt_ja=Enthronement Festival|lt_zh=Enthronement Festival|12=draft}} | The designated successor ascends the throne. |- | {{ill|Coronation (Pharaoh)|de|Krönung (Pharao)|ja|Coronation (Pharaoh)|zh|Coronation (Pharaoh)|lt=Coronation|lt_de=Krönung|lt_ja=Coronation|lt_zh=Coronation|12=draft}}sfest | The throne holder receives the {{ill|Throne Name|de|Thronname|ja|Throne Name|zh|Throne Name|12=draft}} and the crown after the burial of his predecessor. |- | {{ill|Unification Festival|de|Vereinigungsfest (Altes Ägypten)|ja|Unification Festival|zh|Unification Festival|lt=Unification Festival|lt_de=Vereinigungsfest|lt_ja=Unification Festival|lt_zh=Unification Festival|12=draft}} in the Coronation Festival | Symbolic unification of {{ill|Upper Egypt|de|Oberägypten|ja|Upper Egypt|zh|Upper Egypt|lt=Upper-|lt_de=Ober-|lt_ja=Upper-|lt_zh=Upper-|12=draft}} and {{ill|Lower Egypt|de|Unterägypten|ja|Lower Egypt|zh|Lower Egypt|lt=Lower Egypt|lt_de=Unterägypten|lt_ja=Lower Egypt|lt_zh=Lower Egypt|12=draft}}. |- | Daily Renewal | The king ''appears together with {{ill|Ra (Egyptian Mythology)|de|Re (Ägyptische Mythologie)|ja|Ra (Egyptian Mythology)|zh|Ra (Egyptian Mythology)|lt=Ra|lt_de=Re|lt_ja=Ra|lt_zh=Ra|12=draft}}'' every morning. |- | Royal Coronation Festival | As an annual renewal following the completion of a {{ill|Ecliptic#Introduction|de|Ekliptik#Einführung|ja|Ecliptic#Introduction|zh|Ecliptic#Introduction|lt=Solar Path|lt_de=Sonnenbahn|lt_ja=Solar Path|lt_zh=Solar Path}} marking the beginning of a new cycle. |- | {{ill|Min Festival|de|Min-Fest|ja|Min Festival|zh|Min Festival|12=draft}} | Royal renewal and confirmation festival. |- | {{ill|Sokar Festival|de|Sokar-Fest|ja|Sokar Festival|zh|Sokar Festival|12=draft}} | Royal renewal and confirmation festival. |- | {{ill|Neheb-kau Festival|de|Neheb-kau-Fest|ja|Neheb-kau Festival|zh|Neheb-kau Festival|12=draft}} | Royal renewal and confirmation festival with New Year characteristics. |- | {{ill|Valley Festival|de|Talfest|ja|Valley Festival|zh|Valley Festival|lt=Valley Festival|lt_de=Tal-Fest|lt_ja=Valley Festival|lt_zh=Valley Festival|12=draft}} | {{ill|New Kingdom|de|Neues Reich|ja|New Kingdom|zh|New Kingdom|12=draft}}: royal renewal and confirmation festival. |- | {{ill|Amun-Re Festival|de|Amun-Re-Fest|ja|Amun-Re Festival|zh|Amun-Re Festival|12=draft}} | New Kingdom: royal renewal and confirmation festival. |- | {{ill|Opet Festival|de|Opet-Fest|ja|Opet Festival|zh|Opet Festival|12=draft}} | New Kingdom: royal renewal and confirmation festival. |- | {{ill|Sed Festival|de|Sedfest|ja|Sed Festival|zh|Sed Festival|lt=Sed Festival|lt_de=Sed-Fest|lt_ja=Sed Festival|lt_zh=Sed Festival|12=draft}} | Royal renewal and confirmation festival. |- | Death of the King | Burial by his designated successor and transition into the {{ill|Duat|de|Duat|ja|Duat|zh|Duat|12=draft}} as ''son of {{ill|Osiris|de|Osiris|ja|Osiris|zh|Osiris|12=draft}}''. |- |}
=== Cult of the Dead and Divine Festivals === In contrast, {{ill|Cult of the Dead|de|Totenkult|ja|Cult of the Dead|zh|Cult of the Dead|lt=Funerary Festivals|lt_de=Totenfeste|lt_ja=Funerary Festivals|lt_zh=Funerary Festivals|12=draft}} did not fall within the category of royal festivals and fundamentally differed in their festive character. The same applies to ceremonies dedicated to deities that were not directly connected to the reigning king.
