e|Oberägypten|ja|Upper Egypt|zh|Upper Egypt|lt=Upper-|lt_de=Ober-|lt_ja=Upper-|lt_zh=Upper-|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Upper Egypt|qq=}} and {{ill|Lower Egypt|de|Unterägypten|ja|Lower Egypt|zh|Lower Egypt|lt=Lower Egypt|lt_de=Unterägypten|lt_ja=Lower Egypt|lt_zh=Lower Egypt|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Lower Egypt|qq=}}. |- | Daily Renewal | The king ''appears together with {{ill|Ra (Egyptian Mythology)|de|Re (Ägyptische Mythologie)|ja|Ra (Egyptian Mythology)|zh|Ra (Egyptian Mythology)|lt=Ra|lt_de=Re|lt_ja=Ra|lt_zh=Ra|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ra (Egyptian Mythology)|qq=}}'' every morning. |- | Royal Coronation Festival | As an annual renewal following the completion of a {{ill|Ecliptic#Introduction|de|Ekliptik#Einführung|ja|Ecliptic#Introduction|zh|Ecliptic#Introduction|lt=Solar Path|lt_de=Sonnenbahn|lt_ja=Solar Path|lt_zh=Solar Path|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ecliptic#Introduction|qq=}} marking the beginning of a new cycle. |- | {{ill|Min Festival|de|Min-Fest|ja|Min Festival|zh|Min Festival|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Min Festival|qq=}} | Royal renewal and confirmation festival. |- | {{ill|Sokar Festival|de|Sokar-Fest|ja|Sokar Festival|zh|Sokar Festival|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sokar Festival|qq=}} | Royal renewal and confirmation festival. |- | {{ill|Neheb-kau Festival|de|Neheb-kau-Fest|ja|Neheb-kau Festival|zh|Neheb-kau Festival|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Neheb-kau Festival|qq=}} | Royal renewal and confirmation festival with New Year characteristics. |- | {{ill|Valley Festival|de|Talfest|ja|Valley Festival|zh|Valley Festival|lt=Valley Festival|lt_de=Tal-Fest|lt_ja=Valley Festival|lt_zh=Valley Festival|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Valley Festival|qq=}} | {{ill|New Kingdom|de|Neues Reich|ja|New Kingdom|zh|New Kingdom|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/New Kingdom|qq=}}: royal renewal and confirmation festival. |- | {{ill|Amun-Re Festival|de|Amun-Re-Fest|ja|Amun-Re Festival|zh|Amun-Re Festival|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Amun-Re Festival|qq=}} | New Kingdom: royal renewal and confirmation festival. |- | {{ill|Opet Festival|de|Opet-Fest|ja|Opet Festival|zh|Opet Festival|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Opet Festival|qq=}} | New Kingdom: royal renewal and confirmation festival. |- | {{ill|Sed Festival|de|Sedfest|ja|Sed Festival|zh|Sed Festival|lt=Sed Festival|lt_de=Sed-Fest|lt_ja=Sed Festival|lt_zh=Sed Festival|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sed Festival|qq=}} | Royal renewal and confirmation festival. |- | Death of the King | Burial by his designated successor and transition into the {{ill|Duat|de|Duat|ja|Duat|zh|Duat|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Duat|qq=}} as ''son of {{ill|Osiris|de|Osiris|ja|Osiris|zh|Osiris|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Osiris|qq=}}''. |- |}
=== Cult of the Dead and Divine Festivals === In contrast, {{ill|Cult of the Dead|de|Totenkult|ja|Cult of the Dead|zh|Cult of the Dead|lt=Funerary Festivals|lt_de=Totenfeste|lt_ja=Funerary Festivals|lt_zh=Funerary Festivals|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Cult of the Dead|qq=}} did not fall within the category of royal festivals and fundamentally differed in their festive character. The same applies to ceremonies dedicated to deities that were not directly connected to the reigning king.
