|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} marking the beginning of a new cycle. |- | [[:en:Min festival|Min Festival]] | Royal renewal and confirmation festival. |- | {{ill|Sokar Festival|de|Sokar-Fest|ja|Sokar Festival|zh|Sokar Festival|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sokar Festival|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} | Royal renewal and confirmation festival. |- | {{ill|Nehebkau Festival|de|Neheb-kau-Fest|ja|Nehebkau Festival|zh|Nehebkau Festival|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nehebkau Festival|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} | Royal renewal and confirmation festival with New Year characteristics. |- | [[:en:Beautiful Festival of the Valley|Valley Festival]] | [[:en:New Kingdom of Egypt|New Kingdom]]: royal renewal and confirmation festival. |- | {{ill|Amun-Re Festival|de|Amun-Re-Fest|ja|Amun-Re Festival|zh|Amun-Re Festival|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Amun-Re Festival|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} | New Kingdom: royal renewal and confirmation festival. |- | [[:en:Opet Festival|Opet Festival]] | New Kingdom: royal renewal and confirmation festival. |- | [[:en:Sed festival|Sed Festival]] | Royal renewal and confirmation festival. |- | Death of the King | Burial by his designated successor and transition into the [[:en:Duat|Duat]] as ''son of [[:en:Osiris|Osiris]]''. |- |}
=== Cult of the Dead and Divine Festivals === In contrast, [[:en:Mortuary cult|Funerary Festivals]] did not fall within the category of royal festivals and fundamentally differed in their festive character. The same applies to ceremonies dedicated to deities that were not directly connected to the reigning king.
